==English==

===Noun Phrase===
'''[[dirty]] [[wound]]''' (''plural'': '''[[dirty wounds]]''')

# An [[external]] [[wound]], primarily an [[untreated]] cut or tear of the [[skin]], easily susceptible to [[infection]] as a result of exposure to [[unsanitary]] conditions, as would be likely at time of injury.

====Synonyms====
*(''wound that is infected or is susceptible to infection''): [[contaminated wound]], [[infected wound]]

====Antonyms====
*(''wound that is infected or is susceptible to infection''): [[clean wound]], [[septic wound]]

